<li><p>the primary process to make it typically involves brewing, i.e. steeping something in water. For beer it''s cereals or grains to extract something, that something is usually mainly carbohydrates, but also color, flavor and aroma.</p></li>
<li><p>fermentation is used to convert the brew liquor (wort) into beer. There are unfermented "beers" such as the Norwegian "vrterl" (wort-Ale) but these aren''t strictly beers. Fermentation is usually by yeast, Saccaromyces cerevisiae (ales) or S. uvarum (lagers) but other yeasts (S. Brettanomyces) or bacteria (such as lactobacillus) may be used. </p></li>
